==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Warfare
<hw>War"fare`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>War</ets> +
OE. <ets>fare</ets> a journey, a passage, course, AS. <ets>faru.</ets>
See <er>Fare</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Military service; military life; contest carried on
by enemies; hostilities; war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The Philistines gathered their armies together for
<qex>warfare</qex>, to fight with Israel.</q> <rj><qau>I Sam. xxviii.
1.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This day from battle rest;⟦br⟧
Faithful hath been your <qex>warfare</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contest; struggle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The weapons of our <qex>warfare</qex> are not carnal.</q>
<rj><qau>2 Cor. x. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warfare</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Warfare
<hw>War"fare`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To lead a military life; to
carry on continual wars.</def> <rj><au>Camden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Warfarer</ent>⟦br⟧
